p://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Funerary epitaph for Phaino\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n                \u003Cfunder>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\n                \u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"VM\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511\">Valentina Mignosa\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>encoding text division\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"AA\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>Epidoc editing and addition of metadata\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"VF\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6302-3726\">Victoria Fendel\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>lemmatization and linguistic analysis\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic001159\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">492771\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\">39102315\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\">140644\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001159\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-18\">10.5281/zenodo.4351665\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Termini Imerese\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/066\">Museo Civico Baldassare Romano\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">147\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\n                                    \u003Cp>Large slab of grey/brown stone. Forms a pair with \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001160\">ISic001160\u003C/ref>, as they are similar in size, material, and the form and shape of the letters. All sides are almost square, but for the broken top left corner. The back is almost flat, but there is a slight taper on the sides towards the back\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/2.html\">stone (grey)\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">22.8\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">32.5\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">9.5\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n                            \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\n                                    \u003Cp>Three lines of Greek text, roughly centred on stone. Clear use of inscribed guidelines on top and bottom of each line.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                    \u003Cdamage/>\n                                \u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\n                                \u003Cp>Letters are extremely regular and neat, with letter heights all identical (except for phi in line 1, which extends above the guideline). Letters are thin, tall and evenly spaced. Terminal dots carved on all letters. Use of the classic zeta in line 2.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line3\">Lines 1-3\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"39\" atMost=\"39\">39 (phi in line 1: 49mm)\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462513\">Thermae Himeraeae\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/6539140\">Termini Imerese\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003Cgeo>37.98365, 13.69555\u003C/geo>\n                            \u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0101\" notAfter-custom=\"0200\" cert=\"low\">2nd century CE (?)\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\">The place, date, and circumstances of the discovery are unknown, but the inscription is assumed to come from Termini Imerese\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" when=\"2023-07-06\" resp=\"#AA\">Antoniou, 2023-07-06. In the Depositi of Museo Civico Baldassare Romano, room 1, scaffold 12, shelf 3\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n            \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n            \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                    \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/xi:fallback>\n            \u003C/xi:include>\n            \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n                \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                    \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/xi:fallback>\n            \u003C/xi:include>\n        \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#VM\">Valentina Mignosa encoded text division\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-18\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2024-04-24\" who=\"#AA\">edition on basis of autopsy\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2025-07-24\" who=\"#VF\">Victoria Fendel's lemmatizations were added\u003C/change>\n            \u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001159_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001159.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n        \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#VM #AA\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>\u003Cw n=\"5\">Φαινοῖ\u003C/w>\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname type=\"patronym\">\u003Cw n=\"10\">Ζωπύρου\u003C/w>\u003C/name>\u003C/persName>\u003C/persName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003Cw n=\"15\">χαῖρε\u003C/w>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"simple-lemmatized\" resp=\"#VF\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Cw n=\"5\" lemma=\"Φαινώ\">Φαινοῖ\u003C/w>\n                    \u003Cw n=\"10\" lemma=\"Ζωπύρης\">Ζωπύρου\u003C/w>\n                    \u003Cw n=\"15\" lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε\u003C/w>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\n                        \u003Cnote>Text from autopsy\u003C/note>\n                    \u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#AA\">\n                \u003Cp>Phaino, of Zopyros, goodbye!\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>The simple use of the genitive for Zopyros means that we cannot tell whether Phaino is his wife or daughter. Given, however, the similarities with \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001160\">ISic001160\u003C/ref>, it is likely that this is the same man, therefore we can reconstruct his name as Zopyros son of Artemon. There are half a dozen other mentions of the name Zopyros in Sicily and it is quite common elsewhere, whereas Phanoi is rarer, appearing in an inscription from Athens (CIG. I.1013).\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IG\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>\n                            \u003Cref target=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\">340.1\u003C/ref>\n                        \u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IGMusTermini\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Brugnone\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1974\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>11\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/9WZ7KU5C\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl/>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\n                    \u003Cbibl/>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
